id: Organizational Skills 1 Day Training-PH: + Washington, DC United States-Event Brite
name: Organizational Skills 1 Day Training
description:
Through Organizational Skills you will encounter improved productivity, better management, and an overall increase in professional growth.
Everyday people waste numerous amounts of time looking for items.
So stop looking for those important items, and start knowing where they are by getting organized.
Target Audience: Anybody who is interested in learning Organizational Skills.
Learning Objectives:● By the end of this course you will be able to: Remove the Clutter Prioritize Scheduling Your Time To Do Lists Paper and Paperless Storage Organization Your Work Area Tools to Fight Procrastination Organizing your Inbox Avoid the Causes of Disorganization Discipline is the Key to Stay Organized Prerequisites: None Course Materials: Attendees will receive a course manual with presentation slides and reference materials.

id: The Disciplinary Process- Te Awe Awe Street Palmerston North, Manawatū-Whanganui-Event Brite
name: The Disciplinary Process
venue: Te Awe Awe Street Palmerston North, Manawatū-Whanganui
description:
This course will cover how to effectively manage the disciplinary process.
This is where the disciplinary process followed has resulted in the employee taking personal grievance action, claiming they have been unjustifiably dismissed or disadvantaged.
Key audience: This course is suitable for HR practitioners and managers who are responsible for the disciplinary process in their organisations.
Learning outcomes Understand procedural fairness and justifiable reasons for initiating disciplinary action.
Improve supporting documentation such as letter-writing, note-taking and investigative materials.

id: Coffee + Yap-a Allen Street Wellington, Wellington Region-Event Brite
name: Coffee + Yap
venue: a Allen Street Wellington, Wellington Region
description:
Coffee & Yap ☕️🫶 — A Girlss Offline Pop-Up Come join us for a cosy morning of good chats, great coffee, and even better company!
Girlss Offline is all about creating a safe, fun space for wahine in Pōneke to meet new people, connect, and just vibe together — no pressure, no awkward moments.
Whether you're coming solo or with a friend, Coffee & Yap is the perfect low-key way to meet like-minded girlies.
We’ll have conversation starters on hand to help break the ice, food and drinks provided, and the event will be hosted by us, so you won’t be left standing awkwardly with no one to talk to — promise 💛 ✨ What’s included: Coffee, tea & food, conversation starters to spark real chats, curated goodie bag for each guest and a chill, welcoming space to make new connections.
Spots are limited so grab yours early!

id: It's in the Ballot-KCDC- Thursday 21st August Production Day Pass-In-studio- Utauta Street Waikanae, Wellington-Event Brite
name: It's in the Ballot-KCDC- Thursday 21st August Production Day Pass-In-studio
description:
Contestants of 'It's in the Bag' become political candidates in 'It's in the Ballot' Meet the Candidates.
Candidates choose a numbered box which has a question that has been submitted online by voters before the show.
It’s in the Ballot” is a community-led awareness and participation initiative.
We aim to increase voter interest in the general and council elections nationally.
By using broadcasting and web-based technologies to deliver in-studio; online on Facebook, YouTube and Twitch; and edited as YouTube videos we aim to enable voters to make informed voting decisions.

id: Masterclass – Taumata Kōrero with Alexandre O. Philippe-Entrance D, Block Massey Unviersity, Wallace St Mount Cook, Wellington-Event Brite
name: Masterclass – Taumata Kōrero with Alexandre O. Philippe
venue: Entrance D, Block Massey Unviersity, Wallace St Mount Cook, Wellington
description:
Take a peek under the hood and get an inside look at the creative process as Swiss-American filmmaker Alexandre O. Philippe leads this special masterclass, with a focus on film history, deep analysis, and the art of cinematic storytelling.
Known for his distinctive approach to the cinema essay, including NZIFF 2025’s Chain Reactions Alexandre invites participants into a world where film is not just watched, but rigorously examined, deconstructed, and cherished.
A must-attend for filmmakers, critics, students, and film lovers alike, this masterclass promises to ignite your curiosity and sharpen your analytical eye.
Bring your questions, your obsessions, and your love for movies – this is cinephilia at its most alive and engaged.
Members of a number of Film Industry Guilds qualify for concession priced tickets to this Masterclass.

id: After Austen: Em- Willis Street Wellington, Wellington-Event Brite
name: After Austen: Em
description:
We are so excited to welcome award-winning playwright Sam Brooks, to discuss his play Em, a queer retelling of Jane Austen’s masterwork Emma, turned around, flipped and set in our very own Queenstown.
Emmett Woodhouse, handsome, clever and rich, with a comfortable home and a gay disposition has lived nearly [redacted] years in the world with very little to distress or vex him.
Until now.
Attendees get an exclusive 10% discount at Unity Books Sam Brooks is an award-winning and prolific playwright and journalist, who is largely noted for his critically acclaimed LGBTQ+ work, including Riding in Cars with (Mostly Straight) Boys, Queen, and most recently This is My Story of Us, which was co-winner of the 2024 Adam New Zealand Play Award.
He has been shortlisted multiple years for the Adam New Zealand Play Award, and won the Dean Parker award in 2023.

id: Organizational Skills 1 Day Training-PH: + Washington, DC United States-Event Brite
name: Organizational Skills 1 Day Training
description:
Through Organizational Skills you will encounter improved productivity, better management, and an overall increase in professional growth.
Everyday people waste numerous amounts of time looking for items.
So stop looking for those important items, and start knowing where they are by getting organized.
Target Audience: Anybody who is interested in learning Organizational Skills.
Learning Objectives:● By the end of this course you will be able to: Remove the Clutter Prioritize Scheduling Your Time To Do Lists Paper and Paperless Storage Organization Your Work Area Tools to Fight Procrastination Organizing your Inbox Avoid the Causes of Disorganization Discipline is the Key to Stay Organized Prerequisites: None Course Materials: Attendees will receive a course manual with presentation slides and reference materials.

id: The Disciplinary Process- Te Awe Awe Street Palmerston North, Manawatū-Whanganui-Event Brite
name: The Disciplinary Process
venue: Te Awe Awe Street Palmerston North, Manawatū-Whanganui
description:
This course will cover how to effectively manage the disciplinary process.
This is where the disciplinary process followed has resulted in the employee taking personal grievance action, claiming they have been unjustifiably dismissed or disadvantaged.
Key audience: This course is suitable for HR practitioners and managers who are responsible for the disciplinary process in their organisations.
Learning outcomes Understand procedural fairness and justifiable reasons for initiating disciplinary action.
Improve supporting documentation such as letter-writing, note-taking and investigative materials.

id: Beginner Latte Art Class – Learn to Pour with The Hangar Crew- Dixon Street Wellington, Wellington Region-Event Brite
name: Beginner Latte Art Class – Learn to Pour with The Hangar Crew
description:
Whether you're a coffee lover, a home barista, or just curious, this beginner Latte Art Class is for you!

You’ll learn how to texture milk properly and pour a range of basic designs with confidence.
No experience needed All equipment and milk provided Hands-on, small group format Date: Thursday, 14th of August Time: 1700 Cost: $150 per person Very limited spots, book now!
Accessibility: The Hangar is wheelchair accessible and has gender-neutral bathrooms.
